videoSnippet.title: Play the Sveshnikov, They Said || Harikrishna vs Cori || FIDE Chess.com Nations Cup (2020)
videoSnippet.description:
Follow me on Instagram for extra content and notifications https://www.instagram.com/agadmator/

Pentala Harikrishna vs Jorge Cori
FIDE Chess.com Online Nations Cup (2020), 8.5.2020
Sicilian, Labourdonnais-Loewenthal (Kalashnikov) variation (B32)

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e5 5. Nb5 d6 6. N1c3 a6 7. Na3 b5 8. Nd5 Nf6 9. Bg5 Be7 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. c4 b4 12. Nc2 Rb8 13. b3 a5 14. g3 O-O 15. Bg2 g6 16. Nxf6+ Qxf6 17. O-O Qe7 18. Qe2 Be6 19. Rad1 f6 20. Rd3 Nd8 21. Rfd1 Nb7 22. h4 Rfd8 23. Qd2 Kg7 24. Ne3 Rd7 25. f4 Rbd8 26. f5 Bg8 27. fxg6 hxg6 28. Ng4 Bh7 29. Rf3 Rf8 30. Qh6+ Kh8 31. Nxe5

The FIDE Chess.com Online Nations Cup is a 6-team double round-robin tournament taking place from 5-10 May 2020. Teams consist of 6 players, with 4 playing in each round. At least one woman must play in each match.

Players receive 25 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. No draw offers are allowed before move 30. The top 2 after the round-robin will play a Superfinal. Official website: chess.com
